2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the impact of transposition errors in diffusion-based channels, which is a topic relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes strategies to mitigate transpositions in pure diffusion-based channels, which is a topic related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of information using individual particles, which is a topic related to multimedia. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the reliability and capacity of molecular communication, which is a topic relevant to cryptography and security.
